whereas.text:
Whereas children represent the hopes and dreams of the
			 people of the United States and children are the center of families in the
			 United States;

Whereas the people of the United States should nurture and
			 invest in children to preserve and enhance economic prosperity, democracy, and
			 the spirit of the United States;

Whereas the primary teachers of family values, morality,
			 and culture are parents and family members, and children are responsible for
			 passing on family values, morality, and culture to future generations;

Whereas families should be encouraged to engage in family
			 and community activities that include extended and elderly family members and
			 encourage children to explore and develop confidence;

Whereas the designation of a day to honor the children of
			 the United States will help affirm the significance of family, education, and
			 community for the people of the United States;

